Here's the recommended implementation using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (source-generated):

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Replace with your actual data fetch
        var product = await ProductService.GetProductAsync();
        Name = product.Name;
        Price = product.Price;
        IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public `Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable` properties with `PropertyChanged` notification, plus a `LoadCommand` (`IAsyncRelayCommand`).

**XAML usage** — set `x:DataType` at the page root for compiled bindings:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>
    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='Available: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**
- `[ObservableProperty]` on a **private field** generates the public property + change notification automatically.
- `[RelayCommand]` on an `async Task` method generates `LoadCommand` with built-in `IsRunning`/cancel support.
- `x:DataType` enables compiled bindings (8–20× faster, AOT-safe).
- Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to catch binding errors at build time.

**NuGet:** `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (≥ 8.2).
